Source code -> compile -> test -> package(archive like jar war zip) -> code analysis
Java
Build file - xml format
mvn validate - checks if all necessary information is there and structure is good
mvn compile - compile source code of project
mvn test - test the compiled source code with some unit testing framework.
mvn package - creates archive that can be shipped or distributed such as jar
mvn verify - run checks on results of integration test
mvn install - downloads all dependencies to local
mvn deploy - copies final package to remote repo for sharing

mvn uses pom.xml

mvn clean - removes target folder

/home/username/.m2/repository has maven dependencies
